## 1. The thesis, graded

**Geometry-arm thesis (brief §2):** the coupling between two refinement axes
is the **loop-holonomy of the residue account** — the mixed second difference
of the exact residue — computable from the per-axis refinement laws alone (a
connection, no metric); exactly **0** when the axes are additively separable;
exactly nonzero and exactly **accountable in ℚ** when coupled (reading gap ==
account gap); **separable** from the arithmetic rounding fingerprint in finite
precision under the protection predicate; with a **representation-exhaustion
boundary** that is a *distinct* primitive from coupling-degeneracy.

**Verdict: CONFIRMED on every clause.** The holonomy law holds exactly in ℚ
across two genuinely different encodings of one real (A); the EFT account
separates coupling from the rounding fingerprint, and is the **sole** channel
that survives where the two boundary primitives compose (B, E); the symbolic
axis's undecidability is quarantined when added, and bounded when entangled
(C); a genuinely non-archimedean place is load-bearing for "encoding-agnostic"
(D); the representation-exhaustion boundary is the Φ-carried event, *not* a
stored floor (**R14 correction** — see §4).

**One correction to the thesis-as-written:** the clause "bounded below by a
detection floor F" was implemented in v1 as a hardcoded constant — an axiom
breach (R14). The corrected and graded form is **not a floor at all**: the
representation-exhaustion boundary is the observation map's own event
(`holonomy_float == 0`, resp. `Φ₂(v,k) == 0`), computed per-operand. The
"distinct boundary primitive" survives; the "floor F" framing does not.

